	"system": {
		"description": {
			"value": "<p><strong>Materials:</strong> Snow or ice and powdered ruby worth 1,500 gold. This spell consumes these materials.</p><p><strong>Summoning</strong></p><p>You shape an illusory duplicate of one &amp;reference[beast] or &amp;reference[humanoid] that remains within range for the full casting time. The duplicate appears identical to the original but is a &amp;reference[construct] formed of ice and snow. It has half the hit point maximum of the original, no equipment, and otherwise uses all the statistics of the original creature.</p><ul><li><p><strong>Behavior:</strong> The simulacrum is friendly to you and creatures you designate. It obeys your spoken commands, acts on your initiative in combat, and cannot gain levels, new abilities, or regain expended spell slots.</p></li><li><p><strong>Repair:</strong> If the simulacrum is damaged, you can repair it in an alchemical laboratory by expending rare herbs and minerals worth 100 gp per hit point restored.</p></li><li><p><strong>Duration:</strong> The simulacrum lasts until reduced to 0 hit points, whereupon it reverts to snow and melts instantly. If you cast <em>Simulacrum</em> again, all previously created duplicates are destroyed.</p></li></ul>",
